			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Wow, there sure is a lot of advice here. And now I will add my 2 coppers worth.
<br />

<br />
Open your kit, find all the arrows that are yellow to you. Check the bone hooked and steel point arrows for the one that will cost you the Least to make, then buy the goods and make them, and sell them either Back to the vendor or offer them up for sale as you make them. 
<br />

<br />
That is what I did to get my fletching up to 202, and I made lots of arrows daily this way. You will get skill ups and in the end spend a LOT less money than if you just use them. Although I did use some as I went along, and I would bring the goods to make more when I went out hunting just to use my time a bit more wisely but it did cost me more to do this.
<br />

<br />
My current level is 42 and my fletching is 203 or 204, I make Mitheral warrior arrows for skill now (tunare). I keep 2-3 stacks  for pulling tough mobs that i want to snare / shoot back to the group, and sell the rest because i cant afford to burn 10 stacks. I just use class 1 for pulling Most mobs.
<br />

<br />
As a point of interest, Ive gotten 109 crits with mith arrows, and 85 crits with class 1. So really its all in the roll of the dice (as it were). I spent my money on magic resist gear rather than waste it, and the calls of Ranger Down... are a good bit less because of it.
<br />

<br />
Solderus Dragonsfire
<br />
Morder Rasp<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1065044" target="_blank" class="postlink">Solderus Dragonsfire</a>
<br />
Ranger
<br />
Morden Rasp</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
