			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">With all the talk of arrow pulling here, I feel compelled to add my advice to younger rangers.  Keep a NORMAL (non-magic) arrow in your quiver at all times.
<br />

<br />
Many of the mobs you will try to pull can summon.  After AM3, critting one of those mobs for 1k+ is an almost sure-fire way to get summoned and die before you can count to 10.  Using a non-magical arrow will still aggro the mob, but will cause no damage - eliminating the chance of being summoned.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=542589" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fier`Dal Forest Stalker</a>
<br />
Morell Thule 
<br />
<a href="http://www.theedgers.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Faveo Sulum Ipsemet Ascio</a></span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
