				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I believe this post started out with a discussion about pulling... even though this post is about 2 weeks old I thought I would throw in my two cents:
<br />

<br />
I use CLASS 1 WOOD POINT ARROWS with the (cheapest) large groove nock. We're talkin 4 gp for 100 here (fletching 193, not that ya need it for a 16 trivial). I have found that better arrows do really no more damage and those few shots before the mob closes in is maybe like 2% of its health so  really.... 
<br />

<br />
I personally use a DOT to pull, that way I at least can do so damage during the pull, and the DOt is effective as it runs out before the mob goes down. Also, as the spell is casting I cam have turned around and be ready to move back to my grp before the mob eats me :O
<br />

<br />
An alternative is to pull using Spell: Jolt, that way the MT simply engages them mob as it closes in and it no longer wants to beat on me... NICE pull twig tank! YA DIDN'T EVEN GET BEAT ON!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1109842" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: green">Trelin</span></a>
<br />
54 Human Pathfinder of Karana
